Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the design of a new secrecy transmission scheme and characterizes a new achievable secrecy rate for both discrete memoryless and Gaussian channels. This falls under the purview of information theory.
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with the design of a secrecy transmission scheme for a relay-eavesdropper channel, which is a security-related problem. Hence, it is likely to belong to the cryptography and security sub-category.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the design of a transmission scheme for a relay-eavesdropper channel, which involves network coding and interference. Hence, it is likely to belong to the networking and internet architecture sub-category.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new scheme for the relay-eavesdropper channel, which involves the use of interference and network coding. This falls under the purview of systems and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although this is less likely, the paper deals with the transmission of information over a channel, which can be considered a form of multimedia communication. Hence, it is possible that it belongs to the multimedia sub-category.
